      "Based on the search results, I found information about Claude Code updates around early 2025. Here's what I discovered:\n\n## Claude Code Major Updates - Late 2025 (September-October) \n\nThe search results don't show updates specifically for **February 2025**, but there were significant releases in **September-October 2025**:\n\n### 🚀 **Claude Code 2.0 Release (October 2025)**\n\nThis was a major update with extensive new features:\n\n**Key New Features:**\n1. **VS Code Extension (Beta)** - Native integration with VS Code\n2. **Checkpoint System** - Save/restore functionality using `/rewind` command or double-Esc key\n3. **Upgraded Terminal UI** - Better status visibility and searchable prompt history (Ctrl+R)\n4. **Sonnet 4.5 Integration** - New powerful coding model with superior performance\n\n**Enhanced Development Capabilities:**\n- **Subagents** - Delegate specialized tasks\n- **Hooks** - Automatically trigger operations at specific points\n- **Background Tasks** - Long-running processes that don't block other work\n\n### 📊 **Claude Code 2.1 Updates (January 2026)**\n\nEven more recent updates included:\n- **80+ feature changes** including:\n  - **30+ new features** (Skills hot reload, language settings, Vim operations, MCP dynamic updates)\n  - **40+ bug fixes** (security vulnerabilities, Chinese input, terminal compatibility)\n  - **10+ performance optimizations**\n- **Skills Auto Hot-Reload** - Changes to skill files take effect immediately without restart\n\n---\n\n**Note:** The search results don't show any updates specifically for **February 2025**. The most relevant period was late 2025 (September-October) for the 2.0 release, and then 2.1 updates in early 2026.\n\nWould you like me to search for more specific information about a particular feature or time period?"
