n `/settings`, and switch to Auto (Gemini 3) mode via `/model`\n\n#### 2. **Rendering Engine Refactor**\n- 5 major core improvements to the rendering engine\n- Significantly improved AI programming efficiency\n- Better UI/UX with smoother interactions\n\n#### 3. **Enhanced Extension Support**\n- **Conductor**: Transforms Gemini CLI into an active project manager that:\n  - Follows strict protocols for software functionality and bug fixes\n  - Maintains consistent, high-quality task lifecycles (Context → Spec & Plan → Implement)\n  - Provides deep, persistent project understanding\n- **Endor Labs**: Another major extension plugin update\n\n#### 4. **VSCode Integration** (v0.1.20)\n- Deep integration with VS Code\n- Context-aware intelligent suggestions\n- Native diff comparison functionality\n- Seamless operation in VS Code's integrated terminal\n\n#### 5. **MCP Protocol Enhancements**\n- Command-line management of MCP servers\n- Support for multimodal content\n- Root directory support\n\n#### 6. **User Experience Improvements**\n- Responsive terminal UI\n- Reverse command search\n- Configurable context compression\n- Enhanced multi-directory support via `--include-directories` parameter\n\n### Installation & Upgrade\n\n**Install/Upgrade Commands:**\n```bash\n# Via npm\nnpm install -g @google/gemini-cli@latest\n\n# Via Homebrew (macOS/Linux)\nbrew upgrade gemini-cli\nbrew install gemini-cli\n\n# For preview features\nnpm install -g @google/gemini-cli@preview\n\n# Nightly builds\nnpm install -g @google/gemini-cli@nightly\n```\n\n### Free Tier Benefits\n- **1000 free requests per day**\n- Access to Gemini 2.5 Pro and Gemini 3 models\n- Up to 1 million token context window\n- 60 requests per minute rate limit\n\n### System Requirements\n- Node.js version 20 or higher\n- macOS, Linux, or Windows\n\nThe Gemini CLI continues to see very active development with weekly updates, strong community engagement (51+ contributors), and rapid feature additions. The tool has positioned itself as a serious competitor to other AI coding assistants like Claude Code.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
