` (GitHub)\n- **Description:** Continue is the leading open-source AI code assistant for VS Code and JetBrains\n- **GitHub Stars:** ~27,000+ (as of June 2025)\n- **License:** Open source (MIT)\n- **Language:** TypeScript\n\n**Main Features:**\n- Chat interface for code understanding and iteration\n- Autocomplete for inline code suggestions\n- Edit functionality to modify code without leaving files\n- Agent capabilities for substantial codebase changes\n- Support for multiple LLM providers (OpenAI, DeepSeek, local models, etc.)\n- MCP (Model Context Protocol) support\n\n**2025 Configuration Updates:**\n- YAML-based configuration (migrated from JSON format)\n- Support for models like:\n  - Qwen 2.5\n  - DeepSeek R1\n  - Local OpenAI-compatible models\n  - Various context providers (code, docs, terminal, folder, codebase)\n\n**Official Resources:**\n- GitHub: https://github.com/continuedev/continue\n- Documentation: https://docs.continue.dev/getting-started/install\n- Configuration Reference: https://docs.continue.dev/reference\n\n**Note:** The search results primarily show v1.1.8 as the most recent 2025 release. For the complete changelog and detailed release notes, I recommend visiting the official GitHub repository's Releases page directly, as the search results didn't include detailed changelog information beyond version numbers and release dates.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
